ome of up to R350 000 in December – hours before the start of the ANC's elective conference.This will be phased over a five-year period and excludes post graduate students. At the time, National Treasury said details of how "free education" would be funded would be provided in Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba's budget speech in February. http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/sa-will-have-a-fee-based-not-free-education-in-2018-universities-sa-20180108
